    "<view-title>{{ vm.activeGroup == 2? 'Create Platform' : vm.platforms[vm.activePlatform].name }} · Development Platforms</view-title><meta name=description content=\"{{ vm.activeGroup == 2? 'Create Development Platform' : vm.platforms[vm.activePlatform].description | truncate : 200 }}\" view-head><meta name=keywords content=\"embedded, platform, {{ vm.activeGroup == 2? 'creating' : vm.platforms[vm.activePlatform].name }}\" view-head><div class=jumbotron><div class=container><h1><i class=\"fa fa-laptop\"></i> Development Platforms</h1><p><i>Embedded</i> and <i>Desktop</i> development platforms with pre-built toolchains, debuggers, uploaders and frameworks which work under popular host OS: <i class=\"fa fa-apple\"></i> <i>Mac</i>, <i class=\"fa fa-linux\"></i> <i>Linux <small>(+ARM)</small></i> and <i class=\"fa fa-windows\"></i> <i>Windows</i>.</p></div></div><div class=container><uib-tabset active=vm.activeGroup><uib-tab ng-repeat=\"group in ['embedded', 'desktop']\" index=$index><uib-tab-heading><h3 ng-if=\"group == 'embedded'\"><a href=/platforms/atmelavr ng-click=\"vm.changePlatform('atmelavr')\">Embedded Platforms</a></h3><h3 ng-if=\"group == 'desktop'\"><a href=/platforms/linux_arm ng-click=\"vm.changePlatform('linux_arm')\">Desktop Platforms</a></h3></uib-tab-heading><br><uib-tabset type=pills active=vm.activePlatform><uib-tab ng-repeat=\"platform in vm.platforms\" index=$index select=vm.changePlatform(platform.type) ng-if=\"(group == 'embedded' && !platform.forDesktop) || (group == 'desktop' && platform.forDesktop)\"><uib-tab-heading><h4><a href=\"/platforms/{{ platform.type }}\">{{ platform.name }}</a></h4></uib-tab-heading><br><p class=lead>{{ platform.description }}</p><div class=\"alert alert-info\" ng-if=!vm.platforms.creating.active><ul class=fa-ul><li><i class=\"fa fa-info-circle fa-lg fa-li\"></i> More detailed information is located in documentation <a href=\"http://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/platforms/{{ platform.type }}.html\" class=alert-link>Platform {{ platform.name }}</a>.</li></ul></div><h2>Packages</h2><table class=\"table table-striped\"><thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Contents<tr ng-repeat=\"package in platform.packages\"><td><span class=\"label label-default\">{{ package }}</span></td><td><span ng-repeat=\"content in vm.packages[package]\"><a href=\"{{ content.url }}\" target=_blank>{{ content.name }}</a><span ng-if=!$last>,&nbsp;</span></span></td></tr></th></tr></thead></table><div ng-if=!platform.forDesktop><h2>Frameworks</h2><table class=\"table table-striped\"><thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Description<tr ng-repeat=\"framework in vm.frameworks\" ng-if=\"vm.isCompatibleFramework(framework.type, platform.type)\"><td class=text-nowrap><a href=\"/frameworks/{{ framework.type }}\">{{ framework.name }}</a></td><td>{{ framework.description }}</td></tr></th></tr></thead></table><h2>Boards</h2>To list compatible boards with <b>Platform {{ platform.name }}</b> please use <a href=\"/boards?filter%5Bplatform%5D={{ platform.type }}\" class=\"btn btn-success\" role=button>Embedded Boards Explorer</a> or <a href=\"http://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/platforms/{{ platform.type }}.html#boards\">documentation for {{ platform.name }} platform</a>.</div></uib-tab></uib-tabset></uib-tab><uib-tab index=2 select=\"vm.changePlatform('creating')\"><uib-tab-heading><h3><a href=/platforms/creating><i class=\"fa fa-plus\"></i> Create Platform</a></h3></uib-tab-heading><br><p class=lead><b>PlatformIO</b> was developed like a tool which can build the same source code for the different development platforms via single command <a href=http://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/userguide/cmd_run.html><i class=\"fa fa-angle-right fa-lg\"></i> platformio run</a> without any dependent software or requirements.<br><br>For this purpose <i>PlatformIO</i> uses own pre-configured platforms data: build scripts, toolchains, the settings for the most popular embedded boards and etc. These data are pre-built and packaged to the different \"packages\".<br><br>It allows <i>PlatformIO</i> to have multiple development platforms which can use the same packages(toolchains, frameworks), but have different/own build scripts, uploader and etc.</p><p class=text-center><a href=http://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/platforms/creating_platform.html class=\"btn btn-success btn-lg\" role=button target=_blank><i class=\"fa fa-plus fa-lg\"></i> Create Platform</a></p></uib-tab></uib-tabset></div>"
